{"title_page": "Everglow", "text_new": "{{short description|South Korean girl group}}\n{{about|the South Korean girl\n\n| name             = Everglow\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = Everglow at Music Bank on April 19, 2019.png\n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = yes\n| caption          = Everglow in April 2019<br />From left to right: Sihyeon, Onda, E:U, Yiren, Mia and Aisha\n| alias            = \n| origin           = [[Seoul]], South Korean\n| genre            = [[K-pop]]\n| years_active     = 2019\u2013present\n| label            = [[Yuehua Entertainment|Yuehua]]\n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = \n| current_members  = * E:U\n* [[Kim Si-hyeon|Sihyeon]]\n* Mia\n* Onda\n* Aisha\n* Yiren\n}}\n\n'''Everglow''' (\uc5d0\ubc84\uae00\ub85c\uc6b0, stylized as EVERGLOW) is a South Korean girl group under [[Yuehua Entertainment]]. The group is composed of six members: E:U, [[Kim Si-hyeon|Sihyeon]], Mia, Onda, Aisha, and Yiren. Everglow debuted on March 18, 2019, with the single album ''[[Arrival of Everglow]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=311&aid=0000956355|title='\ud504\ub4c048' \uc2dc\ud604X\uc774\ub7f0, \uc704\uc5d0\ud654 \uccab \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 '\uc5d0\ubc84\uae00\ub85c\uc6b0' \ub370\ubdd4 \ud655\uc815 [\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5]|date=February 18, 2019|website=Naver|language=ko|access-date=March 9, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://star.hankookilbo.com/News/Read/201903041166765496|title=\uc5d0\ubc84\uae00\ub85c\uc6b0, 3\uc6d4 \uc815\uc2dd \ub370\ubdd4 \ud0c0\uc774\ud3ec \ud2f0\uc800 \uacf5\uac1c\u2026\uc0c9\ub2e4\ub978 \ucf58\uc149\ud2b8 \uc608\uace0|date=March 3, 2019|website=Hankook Ilbo|language=ko|access-date=March 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n===Pre-debut===\nSihyeon competed in the [[Produce 101 (season 1)|first season]] of [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s reality television competition ''[[Produce 101]]'' in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tv.naver.com/v/663803/|title=\uac1c\uc778\uc5f0\uc2b5\uc0dd \uae40\uc2dc\ud604 \uc5c9\ub6b1\ubc1c\ub784 \ud53c\uce58 \uc18c\ub140 \uc790\uae30 \uc18c\uac1c|website=tv.naver.com}}</ref> She finished in 40th place and subsequently signed with Yuehua Entertainment. Sihyeon returned to the competition at the third season called [[Produce 48]] alongside fellow trainees [[Choi Ye-na|Yena]] and Yiren. While Yena became a member of the girl group [[Iz One]], Sihyeon and Yiren were eliminated in the eleventh episode, finishing in 27th and 28th place respectively.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=421&aid=0003847072|title=\uc5d0\ubc84\uae00\ub85c\uc6b0 \uc2dc\ud604\u00b7\uc774\ub7f0, '\ud504\ub4c048' \ud6c4 \uccab \uacf5\uc2dd \ud65c\ub3d9\u2026SNS '\ud65c\ubc1c'|website=entertain.naver.com}}{{not in source|date=June 2019}}</ref>\n\nOnda, under the name Jo Se-rim, competed on Mnet's reality television competition ''[[Idol School (2017 TV series)|Idol School]]'' in 2017. She was eliminated in the fourth episode, finishing in 40th place.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=144&aid=0000505675|title='\uc544\uc774\ub3cc\ud559\uad50' \uc870\uc138\ub9bc\u00b7\ud64d\uc2dc\uc6b0 \ub4f1 8\uba85 \ud1f4\ucd9c\uc790 \ubc1c\ud45c|website=entertain.naver.com}}</ref>\n\nOn February 17, 2019, Yuehua Entertainment revealed that they would debut a new girl group named Everglow. The group's official [[Instagram]] and fan cafe opened on February 18.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/ko-kr/entertainment/music/\uc704\uc5d0\ud654-\uc0c8-\uadf8\ub8f9-\uc5d0\ubc84\uae00\ub85c\uc6b0-everglow-\uacf5\uc2dd-sns-\uac1c\uc124\u2026\ubcf4\uc774\uadf8\ub8f9-\uc544\ub2cc-\uac78\uadf8\ub8f9/ar-BBTHGnh|title=\uc704\uc5d0\ud654 \uc0c8 \uadf8\ub8f9 \uc5d0\ubc84\uae00\ub85c\uc6b0(EVERGLOW), \uacf5\uc2dd SNS \uac1c\uc124\u2026'\ubcf4\uc774\uadf8\ub8f9 \uc544\ub2cc \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9'|date=February 18, 2019|website=msn|language=ko|access-date=March 9, 2019}}</ref> The company revealed the members of the group through the \"Crank in Film\" series on [[Stone Music Entertainment]]'s YouTube Channel.\nEverglow's concept photos were released on March 8.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.sedaily.com/NewsView/1VGGJA5KIA|title=\uad34\ubb3c\uc2e0\uc778 '\uc5d0\ubc84\uae00\ub85c\uc6b0'3\uc6d4 \ucd9c\uaca9...\ud0c0\uc774\ud3ec \ud2f0\uc800 \uacf5\uac1c\ub85c \ub370\ubdd4 \uc2e0\ud638\ud0c4|date=March 4, 2019|website=sedaily|language=ko|access-date=March 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2019\u2013present: Debut with ''Arrival of Everglow'', ''Hush'' and ''Reminiscence''===\n[[File:Everglow at Music Bank on April 12, 2019.png|thumb|Everglow in April 2019]]\nOn March 18, 2019, Everglow released their first single album, ''[[Arrival of Everglow]]'', with the lead single \"Bon Bon Chocolat\". The song was co-written by the American singer-songwriter [[Melanie Fontana]], who has previously written for established groups including the boy band [[BTS (band)|BTS]] and the singer [[Tiffany Young]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=410&aid=0000562607|title=\uc5d0\ubc84\uae00\ub85c\uc6b0, \ud2b8\ub799\ub9ac\uc2a4\ud2b8 \uacf5\uac1c\u2026\ud0c0\uc774\ud2c0\uace1 '\ubd09\ubd09\uc1fc\ucf5c\ub77c' \uad00\uc2ec UP|date=March 9, 2019|website=Naver|language=ko|access-date=March 10, 2019}}</ref> The group made their debut stage on March 21 on Mnet's music program ''[[M Countdown]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0003393773|title=[\ud3ec\ud1a0] \uc5d0\ubc84\uae00\ub85c\uc6b0 '\ubbf8\uc18c \uc720\ubc1c \ud3ec\uc988'|date=March 21, 2019|website=Naver|language=ko|access-date=March 21, 2019}}</ref> Everglow enjoyed commercial success with their releases; ''Arrival of Everglow'' debuted and peaked at number 6 on the [[Gaon Album Chart]], selling more than 17,000 copies as of July 2019,<ref name=\":0\"/> while \"Bon Bon Chocolat\" debuted and peaked at number 5 on the [[World Digital Song Sales]] Chart.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8504682/everglow-bon-bon-chocolat-top-5-debuton-world-digital-song-sales-chart|title=EVERGLOW Make Top 5 Debut on World Digital Song Sales Chart With 'Bon Bon Chocolat'|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|date=March 28, 2019|website=Billboard|accessdate=March 29, 2019}}</ref> On August 19, 2019, the group released their second single album ''[[Hush (single album)|Hush]]'' with the lead single \"Adios\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8527855/everglow-adios-music-video|title=EVERGLOW Return With Impactful 'Adios': Watch the Music Video|date=August 20, 2019|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Herman|first=Tamar|access-date=February 15, 2020}}</ref> On September 24, 2019, Everglow won their first music program broadcast award on ''[[The Show (South Korean TV series)|The Show]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=076&aid=0003472194|title=[\ud3ec\ud1a0] \uc5d0\ubc84\uae00\ub85c\uc6b0, '\ub354 \uc1fc' 1\uc704\uc5d0 \uac10\uaca9!|date=September 24, 2019|website=Naver|language=ko|access-date=September 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn February 3, 2020, the group released their first mini-album ''[[Reminiscence (EP)|Reminiscence]]'' with the lead single \"Dun Dun\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/213/0001150523|title=\uc5d0\ubc84\uae00\ub85c\uc6b0\uac00 \uc628\ub2e4...2\uc6d43\uc77c 1st \ubbf8\ub2c8\uc568\ubc94 '\ub808\ubbf8\ub2c8\uc120\uc2a4' \ubc1c\ub9e4 [\uacf5\uc2dd]|website=n.news.naver.com}}</ref> On January 21, 2020, it was announced that Everglow will embark on the ''Everlasting Tour in USA'', beginning in [[Dallas]], [[Texas]] on March 6, 2020. The tour would span five different cities in the United States.<ref>{{in lang|ko}} [https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/018/0004561918 \uc5d0\ubc84\uae00\ub85c\uc6b0, \ubbf8\uad6d 5\uac1c \ub3c4\uc2dc\ubd80\ud130 \uccab \uc6d4\ub4dc\ud22c\uc5b4 \ub5a0\ub09c\ub2e4]</ref>\n\n==Members==\nAdapted from their Naver profile.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&sm=tab_ppn&query=\uadf8\ub8f9everglow&os=9572543&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService|title=Everglow Naver Profile|publisher=Naver|language=ko}}</ref>\n* E:U (\uc774\uc720)\n* [[Kim Si-hyeon|Sihyeon]] (\uc2dc\ud604)\n* Mia (\ubbf8\uc544)\n* Onda (\uc628\ub2e4)\n* Aisha (\uc544\uc0e4)\n* Yiren (\uc774\ub7f0)\n\n==Discography==\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of extended plays, with selected details, chart positions, and sales\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\" | Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"4\" style=\"width:5em;\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Sales\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Gaon Music Chart|KOR]]<br><ref>{{cite web |url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T|title=Gaon Album Chart|website=Gaon Chart|accessdate=March 28, 2019|language=ko}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=06&hitYear=2019&termGbn=week|title=Reminiscence|accessdate=February 13, 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Oricon Albums Chart|JPN]]<br><ref>Oricon Albums Chart:\n* {{cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/ja/w/2020-02-17/p/5/|title=Reminiscence|date=February 17, 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard Japan#Billboard Japan charts|JPN<br>Hot]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail/?a=hot_albums|title=Hot Albums|website=Billboard Japan|accessdate=February 12, 2020|language=ja}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=hot_albums&year=2020&month=02&day=17|title=Reminiscence|date=February 17, 2020}}\n</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Billboard cha